          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      {/* ─── Protocol Blocks (:::) ────────────────────────────────
           The triple-colon form is distinct from :: directives —
           it is an authoring surface that compiles to one or more
           :: directives at build time AND renders a UI component.
           Hosted in the syntax spec so authors can find it, but
           the compilation target lives in the Atto Leasing
           Protocol (ALP) spec. */}
      <section id="protocol-blocks">
        <p class="eyebrow">09 — Protocol Blocks</p>
        <h2>Protocol blocks.</h2>
        <p>
          Protocol blocks use the triple-colon form <code>:::name &#123; … &#125; :::</code>.
          Unlike regular <code>::</code> directives, a <code>:::</code> block is an
          authoring surface: it compiles to one or more <code>::</code> directives
          at document build time <em>and</em> renders a UI component the
          subject of the block sees when they open the document.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every <code>:::</code> block is disclosure-first. Fields the author
          might otherwise omit — purpose, requesting party, privacy scope —
          are REQUIRED. The document is invalid if any required disclosure
          field is missing. The tenant (or counterparty, or subject) reads
          the rendered form; an auditor can read the block source and verify
          exactly what consent was granted.
        </p>

        {/* ─── :::credit-check ─────────────────────────────────── */}
        <h3 id="block-credit-check"><code>:::credit-check</code></h3>
        <p>
          Declares a credit-check precondition for document execution. The
          block compiles to an <code>::alp:precondition:credit-check</code>
          directive evaluated by the Precondition Directive Evaluation Engine
          (PDEE), and simultaneously renders a tenant-facing consent form.
          The subject cannot sign the document until the precondition is
          satisfied.
        </p>

        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: var(--text-base); margin-block: var(--space-5) var(--space-2);">Required disclosure fields</h4>
        <FieldTable
          caption=":::credit-check required fields"
          fields={[
            { name: 'id', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'Unique identifier within the document. Referenced by the compiled ::alp:precondition:credit-check directive as precondition_id.' },
            { name: 'party', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'party_id of the subject whose credit is being checked. MUST resolve to a party declared in the execution preamble.' },
            { name: 'purpose', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'Plain-language reason for the check. Shown verbatim in the tenant\'s consent disclosure and reported to the bureau adapter as permissible-purpose context. Template placeholders are rejected.' },
            { name: 'requesting_party', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'Legal name of the entity requesting the check. Shown verbatim in the consent disclosure. MUST match the landlord party\'s legal_name.' },
            { name: 'pull_type', type: "'hard_pull' | 'soft_pull'", required: true, description: 'Hard pulls appear on the consumer\'s credit file; soft pulls do not. A mismatch with the bureau adapter\'s actual pull type is a fatal validation error.' },
            { name: 'bureau', type: "'experian' | 'transunion' | 'equifax' | 'any'", required: true, description: "'any' permits the PDEE to select the bureau. The bureau actually used is recorded in execution metadata." },
            { name: 'score_model', type: "'FICO8' | 'FICO9' | 'VantageScore3' | 'VantageScore4'", required: true, description: 'Scoring model used for the pass/fail determination.' },
            { name: 'disclosed_to', type: 'array of enum | party_id', required: true, description: 'Who receives the pass/fail outcome. Values: requesting_party, named_parties, all_signatories, or specific party_ids. The raw score is NEVER shared through this field — only the pass/fail result.' },
            { name: 'extent', type: "'score_only' | 'full_report' | 'income_verified'", required: true, description: 'Breadth of the inquiry. See the extent reference below.' },
            { name: 'min_score', type: 'integer 300–850', required: true, description: 'Required when extent is score_only or income_verified. Minimum score for a pass outcome.' },
            { name: 'on_pass', type: "'proceed' | 'notify_requesting_party'", required: true, description: 'PDEE action on pass. proceed advances the execution queue.' },
            { name: 'on_fail', type: "'withdraw' | 'notify_requesting_party' | 'human_review'", required: true, description: 'PDEE action on fail. human_review pauses execution for review_window_hours before auto-withdrawing.' },
          ]}
        />

        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: var(--text-base); margin-block: var(--space-6) var(--space-2);">Optional fields</h4>
        <FieldTable
          caption=":::credit-check optional fields"
          fields={[
            { name: 'immediate_feedback', type: 'boolean', required: false, description: 'Default false. When true, the rendered form shows the tenant a pass/fail result as soon as the bureau responds. When false, the tenant sees only a "submitted — awaiting review" state.' },
            { name: 'review_window_hours', type: 'integer', required: false, description: 'Only valid when on_fail = human_review. Default 48. Hours the requesting party has to decide before auto-withdrawal.' },
            { name: 'timeout_hours', type: 'integer', required: false, description: 'Default 48. Hours the PDEE waits for a bureau response before treating the check as failed.' },
          ]}
        />

        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: var(--text-base); margin-block: var(--space-6) var(--space-2);">Extent levels</h4>
        <FieldTable
          caption="extent field values"
          fields={[
            { name: 'score_only', type: 'Score only', required: false, description: 'Credit score only. No tradeline detail, no account history. Lowest privacy impact. min_score is required.' },
            { name: 'full_report', type: 'Full report', required: false, description: 'Full consumer credit report including tradelines, inquiries, public records, and collections. Retained in execution metadata (encrypted, accessible only to requesting party). min_score optional.' },
            { name: 'income_verified', type: 'Score + income', required: false, description: 'Credit score plus income verification via payroll connector (Argyle, Pinwheel). Requires chained ::alp:precondition:income-verify. min_score is required and applies to the score component only.' },
          ]}
        />

        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: var(--text-base); margin-block: var(--space-6) var(--space-2);">Example — residential lease</h4>
        <AttoDemo filename="credit-check.atto" label=":::credit-check">
          <div slot="rendered">
            <CreditCheckBlock
              requestingParty="Westbrook Property Management LLC"
              purpose="Residential tenancy application for 42 Elm Street, Unit 3B, Los Angeles, CA 90024. Requested by Westbrook Property Management LLC on behalf of property owner."
              scoreModel="FICO8"
              bureau="transunion"
              pullType="hard_pull"
              disclosedTo={["Westbrook Property Management LLC"]}
              immediateFeedback={false}
              onFail="human_review"
              reviewWindowHours={72}
            />
          </div>

          <pre class="code-block" slot="source"><code><span class="tok-directive">:::credit-check</span> &#123;
  <span class="tok-key">id</span>               = <span class="tok-string">"cc-residential-001"</span>
  <span class="tok-key">party</span>            = <span class="tok-string">"party-tenant-jane-doe"</span>

  <span class="tok-key">purpose</span>          = <span class="tok-string">"Residential tenancy application for 42 Elm Street,</span>
<span class="tok-string">                      Unit 3B, Los Angeles, CA 90024. Requested by</span>
<span class="tok-string">                      Westbrook Property Management LLC on behalf of</span>
<span class="tok-string">                      property owner."</span>

  <span class="tok-key">requesting_party</span> = <span class="tok-string">"Westbrook Property Management LLC"</span>
  <span class="tok-key">pull_type</span>        = <span class="tok-string">hard_pull</span>
  <span class="tok-key">bureau</span>           = <span class="tok-string">transunion</span>
  <span class="tok-key">score_model</span>      = <span class="tok-string">FICO8</span>

  <span class="tok-key">disclosed_to</span>     = [<span class="tok-string">requesting_party</span>]
  <span class="tok-key">extent</span>           = <span class="tok-string">score_only</span>
  <span class="tok-key">min_score</span>        = <span class="tok-string">680</span>

  <span class="tok-key">on_pass</span>          = <span class="tok-string">proceed</span>
  <span class="tok-key">on_fail</span>          = <span class="tok-string">human_review</span>
  <span class="tok-key">review_window_hours</span> = <span class="tok-string">72</span>

  <span class="tok-key">immediate_feedback</span> = <span class="tok-string">false</span>
  <span class="tok-key">timeout_hours</span>    = <span class="tok-string">24</span>
&#125;
<span class="tok-directive">:::</span></code></pre>
        </AttoDemo>

        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: var(--text-base); margin-block: var(--space-6) var(--space-2);">Compilation to ALP</h4>
        <p>
          The <code>:::credit-check</code> block compiles mechanically to an
          <code>::alp:precondition:credit-check</code> directive at build
          time. The field mapping is exact:
        </p>

        <FieldTable
          caption="Compilation mapping"
          fields={[
            { name: 'id', type: '→ precondition_id', required: false, description: 'Direct mapping.' },
            { name: 'party', type: '→ subject_party_id', required: false, description: 'Direct mapping.' },
            { name: 'min_score / bureau / score_model / pull_type / timeout_hours', type: '→ same', required: false, description: 'Direct mapping of PDEE-relevant fields.' },
            { name: 'on_fail = withdraw', type: '→ failure_action = "withdraw"', required: false, description: 'Document enters WITHDRAWN on fail.' },
            { name: 'on_fail = notify_requesting_party', type: '→ failure_action = "notify_only"', required: false, description: 'Record failure; notify landlord; await their decision.' },
            { name: 'on_fail = human_review', type: '→ failure_action = "notify_only" + review_window annotation', required: false, description: 'Pauses at PRECONDITION_PENDING for review_window_hours.' },
            { name: 'purpose / requesting_party / disclosed_to / extent', type: '→ consent_scope.* fields', required: false, description: 'Embedded in the consent-scope object sent to the bureau adapter as permissible-purpose context.' },
            { name: 'immediate_feedback', type: '→ renderer directive only', required: false, description: 'Not forwarded to the PDEE. Purely controls what the rendered form shows the subject.' },
          ]}
        />

        <h4 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 700; font-size: var(--text-base); margin-block: var(--space-6) var(--space-2);">Validation rules</h4>
        <p>A document containing a <code>:::credit-check</code> block is INVALID if any of the following are true:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>purpose</code> is absent, empty, or contains only template placeholder text (e.g. <code>[property address]</code>).</li>
          <li><code>requesting_party</code> does not match the <code>legal_name</code> of any declared party.</li>
          <li><code>party</code> does not resolve to a <code>party_id</code> in the execution preamble.</li>
          <li><code>pull_type = hard_pull</code> and <code>consent_scope</code> has not been completed before PDEE dispatch.</li>
          <li><code>extent</code> is <code>score_only</code> or <code>income_verified</code> and <code>min_score</code> is absent.</li>
          <li><code>on_fail = human_review</code> and <code>review_window_hours</code> is absent.</li>
          <li><code>disclosed_to</code> contains a party id not declared in the execution preamble.</li>
          <li>Two <code>:::credit-check</code> blocks in the same document share an <code>id</code>.</li>
          <li><code>immediate_feedback = true</code> and <code>on_fail = human_review</code> simultaneously — these are contradictory.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          Raw-score disclosure is non-negotiable: regardless of
          <code>disclosed_to</code>, the numeric score is NEVER exposed in
          the rendered document or any interface accessible to disclosed
          parties. Scores are stored encrypted in execution metadata,
          accessible only to the PDEE and, after execution, to the
          requesting party via a credentialed API call.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      {/* ─── Serialization ────────────────────────────────────── */}
      <section id="serialization">
        <p class="eyebrow">10 — Serialization</p>
        <h2>Serialization rules.</h2>
        <p>
          Serialization is deterministic. Two ASTs that are structurally equal
          serialize to byte-identical output. The implications:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Trailing whitespace is stripped on every line.</li>
          <li>Every block is separated by exactly one blank line.</li>
          <li>YAML keys in frontmatter and directives are sorted alphabetically.</li>
          <li>Line endings are <code>LF</code>, encoding is <code>UTF-8</code>.</li>
          <li>The final byte is a single newline.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This makes <code>git diff</code> reflect semantic change, not
          formatting drift.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      {/* ─── AST Mapping ──────────────────────────────────────── */}
      <section id="ast-mapping">
        <p class="eyebrow">11 — Abstract Syntax Tree</p>
        <h2>Abstract Syntax Tree mapping.</h2>
        <p>
          Each surface construct maps to a node type. The set is closed: the
          parser rejects unknown directives rather than silently passing them
          through.
        </p>
        <pre class="code-block"><code><span class="tok-key">document</span>     → Document &#123; frontmatter, children[] &#125;
<span class="tok-key">##...######</span>   → Section &#123; depth, title, children[] &#125;
<span class="tok-key">paragraph</span>    → Paragraph &#123; inlines[] &#125;
<span class="tok-key">**x**</span>        → Strong &#123; children[] &#125;
<span class="tok-key">*x*</span>          → Emphasis &#123; children[] &#125;
<span class="tok-key">`x`</span>          → Code &#123; value &#125;
<span class="tok-key">[text](url)</span>  → Link &#123; url, children[] &#125;
<span class="tok-key">$x$</span>          → MathInline &#123; tex &#125;
<span class="tok-key">$$x$$</span>        → MathDisplay &#123; tex &#125;
<span class="tok-key">::name</span>       → Directive &#123; name, attrs, body &#125;
<span class="tok-key">:::name</span>      → ProtocolBlock &#123; name, fields, compiled[] &#125;
<span class="tok-key">@/.../...</span>    → FontReference &#123; tier, scope, name, version &#125;</code></pre>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      {/* ─── MVP Scope ────────────────────────────────────────── */}
      <section id="mvp-scope">
        <p class="eyebrow">12 — MVP Scope</p>
        <h2>MVP scope.</h2>
        <p>
          The v0 parser implements the full set described above. The MVP
          runtime implements: frontmatter, sections, inline formatting, inline
          and display LaTeX, and the five core directives. Anything outside
          that set is a post-v0 extension.
        </p>
        <p>
          The signing pipeline targets <code>::signature-block</code> only.
          Other directives have no lifecycle effect in v0 — they render and
          serialize, but do not emit protocol events.
        </p>
        <p>
          Font references parse in v0 with the full identifier grammar, but
          the AFRP resolver — manifest fetch, schema validation, SHA-256
          integrity checks, execution-pin freezing at signing — ships as a
          follow-on milestone. Documents authored today that declare font
          references will be compatible with the resolver when it lands.
        </p>
        <p>
          <code>:::</code> protocol blocks parse in v0 with validation,
          compile to their target <code>::</code> directives, and render
          their UI components. Live precondition evaluation (PDEE dispatch,
          bureau integration) is coordinated through the Atto Leasing
          Protocol spec and ships in the ALP runtime.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>

